message:
feat: Complete submodule support with nested struct bundling

Implements full Python package support with Bun-style single-file bundling.
Packages with submodules compile to nested Zig structs for zero-overhead
native execution.

Architecture:
- Package detection: analyzePackage() identifies packages vs modules
- Nested compilation: Recursive struct generation with qualified names
- Type inference: Multi-level attribute chain resolution
- Allocator passing: Automatic for all nesting levels

Key changes:
- src/import_resolver.zig: PackageInfo struct + analyzePackage()
- src/codegen/native/main/imports.zig: compileModuleAsStructWithPrefix()
- src/analysis/native_types/expressions.zig: buildQualifiedName() helper
- src/codegen/native/expressions/calls.zig: Recursive module call detection

Generated structure:
const testpkg = struct {
    pub fn main_func() { }
    pub const submod = struct {
        pub fn sub_func() { }
    };
};

Works:
- testpkg.main_func() ✅
- testpkg.submod.sub_func() ✅
- testpkg.math.add(10, 20) ✅

Test results: 70/143 passing (baseline maintained)

